roof.js#L319), [scripts/proofs/live_dispatch_proof.md:2](/C:/Users/akima/Desktop/codex_Original_UI_PJ/scripts/proofs/live_dispatch_proof.md#L2).\n- Medium: `stopChild()` does not actually guarantee teardown. After `child.kill(\"SIGTERM\")`, Node sets `child.killed=true` as soon as the signal is sent, so the later `SIGKILL` branch is skipped even if the process never exits. On Windows that can leak proof-run servers and poison later runs/ports. References: [scripts/generate_runtime_proof.js:141](/C:/Users/akima/Desktop/codex_Original_UI_PJ/scripts/generate_runtime_proof.js#L141), [scripts/generate_runtime_proof.js:152](/C:/Users/akima/Desktop/codex_Original_UI_PJ/scripts/generate_runtime_proof.js#L152).\n- Medium: the new runtime proof does not verify the `CODEX_TURN_ARTIFACTS_DIR` override it sets. The script asserts isolated harness memory and eval history paths, but never checks `/api/runtime`’s evidence-artifact root or that emitted turn artifacts landed under the proof-local `turns/` directory. A regression in turn-artifact routing would still produce a passing proof. References: [scripts/generate_runtime_proof.js:217](/C:/Users/akima/Desktop/codex_Original_UI_PJ/scripts/generate_runtime_proof.js#L217), [scripts/generate_runtime_proof.js:245](/C:/Users/akima/Desktop/codex_Original_UI_PJ/scripts/generate_runtime_proof.js#L245), [scripts/generate_runtime_proof.js:256](/C:/Users/akima/Desktop/codex_Original_UI_PJ/scripts/generate_runtime_proof.js#L256), [scripts/generate_runtime_proof.js:465](/C:/Users/akima/Desktop/codex_Original_UI_PJ/scripts/generate_runtime_proof.js#L465).\n\n**Contract-Fit Verdict**\nNot fit. The blocked-default and isolated-path changes are mostly present, but the proof/evidence path does not fully satisfy the documented “isolated proof bundle” contract, and the launcher has a concrete env-handling mismatch.\n\n**Over-Delivery-Fit Verdict**\nNot fit. The added proof flow over-delivers on evidence, but it crosses the boundary into shared repo state via `scripts/proofs/live_dispatch_proof.md`, so the added value is not cleanly bounded.\n\n**Recommendation**\nFAIL\n\nResidual notes: I did not find an obvious governance defect in the current skill catalog / new skill package integration. I also did not find a material bug in the core `server.js` blocked-default normalization itself; the main problems are launcher contract mismatch and proof correctness/evidence quality."}}}}
