t prefer frontend/backend/infra/tester paths\\n\\n## 4) Machine-Readable Contracts\\n\\n- Agent governance:\\n  - `scripts/config/agent_governance_contracts.json`\\n  - defines parent agents, scope paths, read-only and verification-only roles, and `worker` legacy gating\\n- Turn lifecycle:\\n  - `scripts/config/harness_contract_spec.json`\\n  - defines `in_progress -> completed|interrupted|failed` and terminal event `turn/completed`\\n- Task outcome taxonomy:\\n  - `scripts/config/task_outcome_contract.json`\\n  - defines `COMPLETED`, `BLOCKED`, `NEEDS_INPUT`, `FAILED_VALIDATION`, `PARTIAL`\\n\\n## 5) Runtime Surfaces\\n\\n- `GET /api/runtime`\\n  - runtime snapshot, latest turn, governance policy, turn contract, task outcome contract, eval/replay/SLO capability summary\\n- `POST /api/exec`\\n  - authenticated JSON exec endpoint with NDJSON streaming turn events\\n- `GET /api/eval/suites`\\n- `GET /api/eval/history`\\n- `POST /api/eval/run`\\n- `GET /api/replay/turns`\\n- `GET /api/replay/turn/:turnId`\\n- `POST /api/replay/turn`\\n- `GET /api/slo/status`\\n- `GET /api/conversation/runtime`\\n- `POST /api/conversation/direct`\\n\\n## 6) Evidence and Persistence\\n\\n- Turn artifacts are written under `logs/turns/` with `manifest.json` plus events/items/diff/stdout/stderr artifacts.\\n- The turn artifact manifest now records:\\n  - terminal turn status\\n  - terminal task outcome status and reason\\n  - approval audit records\\n  - execution observed signals\\n- Harness memory is stored in `logs/harness_execution_memory.json`.\\n- Replay memory, idempotency snapshots, and latest turn snapshots carry `taskOutcomeStatus` and `taskOutcomeReason`.\\n\\n## 7) Current Completion Gates\\n\\n- `server.js` or `scripts/` changes:\\n  - run `node scripts/app_server_smoke_test.js`\\n- Skill assignment or skill package changes:\\n  - run `node scripts/skill_portfolio_audit.js`\\n- Spec sync before `COMPLETED`:\\n  - update this file\\n  - append a matching entry to `docs/ARCHITECTURE_CHANGELOG.md`\\n\\n## 8) Current Residual Risks\\n\\n- Context and evidence discipline are stronger, but context/memory promotion is still not fully machine-enforced.\\n- `worker` is now runtime-gated, but it still exists as a compatibility lane and should be retired once remaining legacy use disappears.\\n- Some lower-tier operator documents remain mixed-language.\\n\\r\\n\",\"exitCode\":0,\"durationMs\":179}}\nlogs\\turns\\2026-03-07\\019cc56e-796d-75c3-b2f7-f06eeed3af79__019cc6ad-352e-7082-918f-452ced371381\\items.ndjson:437:{\"ts\":\"2026-03-07T05:20:33.376Z\",\"phase\":\"completed\",\"item\":{\"type\":\"commandExecution\",\"id\":\"call_trwPqy4JEHk6rRphcvZbU2Z8\",\"command\":\"\\\"C:\\\\\\\\WINDOWS\\\\\\\\System32\\\\\\\\WindowsPowerShell\\\\\\\\v1.0\\\\\\\\powershell.exe\\\" -Command \\\"Get-Content docs\\\\\\\\ARCHITECTURE_CHANGELOG.md | Select-Object -Last 80\\\"\",\"cwd\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\akima\\\\Desktop\\\\codex_Original_UI_PJ\",\"processId\":null,\"status\":\"completed\",\"commandActions\":[{\"type\":\"unknown\",\"command\":\"Get-Content docs\\\\ARCHITECTURE_CHANGELOG.md | Select-Object -Last 80\"}],\"aggregatedOutput\":\"\\r\\n### Intent\\r\\n- Make the `AGENTS.md` reference map easier to scan by grouping references by contract type instead of only by topic.\\r\\n- Expose `eval_suite_default.json` explicitly as evaluation config without promoting it to core governance contract status.\\r\\n\\r\\n### Implemented\\r\\n- Reorganized `AGENTS.md` reference map into:\\r\\n  - tier-1 operating policies\\r\\n  - protocol/runtime runbook\\r\\n  - machine-readable governance contracts\\r\\n  - machine-readable runtime contract\\r\\n  - evaluation config\\r\\n- Added `scripts/config/eval_suite_default.json` under:\\r\\n  - `Evaluation config (supplemental, non-governance)`\\r\\n\\r\\n### Verification Evidence\\r\\n- Manual reference-map classification review -> PASS\\r\\n  - governance contracts are separated from runtime contract\\r\\n  - evaluation config is